subSubSection.paragraph:
PEREOPODS. Pereopod 3 (distal three articles broken in 
holotype
) slender, merus bearing large produced lobe anterodistally. Pereopod 4 similar to pereopod 3, but coxa much broader. Pereopod 5 slightly longer than pereopod 7, coxa bilobate, anterior lobe smaller than posterior lobe; merus broader than distal three articles, with posterodistal strongly produced as lobe, anterior margin with 4+ groups of 2–3 robust setae; propodus 1.4 times longer than carpus, anterior margin bearing 8 groups of 2–3 bifid robust setae; dactylus slender, with acute tip, evenly tapering, 0.7 length of propodus, with small nail. Pereopod 6 (distal three articles broken in 
holotype
) gill smaller than that of pereopod 5; coxa bilobate, anterior lobe much smaller than posterior lobe; basis slight longer than that of pereopod 5. Pereopod 7 coxa unilobate, rounded; basis broader than that of pereopods 5 and 6, anterior margin bearing robust setae; propodus subequal in length to carpus; dactylus half-length of propodus, with small acute nail.
